    AI Overview
    To boil eggs, place them in a pot, cover with cold water by about an inch, and bring to a rolling boil. Once boiling, turn off the heat, cover the pot, and let the eggs stand in the hot water for 9-12 minutes. Finally, transfer the eggs to an ice bath to stop the cooking and make them easier to peel. 
    This video demonstrates how to boil eggs perfectly, from soft-boiled to hard-boiled:
    01:00
    Lets Eat
    YouTube 3 Oct 2024
    Step 1: Prepare the eggs and water 
    • Place eggs in a single layer in a saucepan large enough to hold them without crowding.
    • Add cold water to cover the eggs by about one inch. 
    Step 2: Bring to a boil 
    • Place the pot over high heat and bring the water to a rolling boil.
    • Once the water reaches a full boil, turn off the heat and immediately cover the pot with a lid. 
    Step 3: Let the eggs stand 
    • Leave the covered pot on the burner for 9 to 12 minutes, depending on your desired doneness.
      • For large eggs: 9 minutes for medium-boiled, 12 minutes for hard-boiled.
      • For medium eggs: about 9 minutes.
      • For extra-large eggs: about 15 minutes. 
    Step 4: Cool the eggs 
    • While the eggs are standing, prepare a bowl of ice water (an ice bath).
    • When the time is up, use a slotted spoon to carefully transfer the eggs from the hot water to the ice bath.
    • Let them cool in the ice bath for at least 10-15 minutes. This stops the cooking process and helps make the shells easier to remove. 
    Step 5: Peel the eggs 
    • Once cool, gently tap an egg on a hard surface, roll it to crack the shell all over, and peel it under cool running water or in the ice water.

    What is the correct way to boil an egg?
    HEAT over high heat just to boiling. REMOVE from burner. COVER pan. LET EGGS STAND in hot water about 12 minutes for large eggs (9 minutes for medium eggs; 15 minutes for extra large).

    Do you put eggs in water before or after it's boiling?
    Always make sure to have your water boiling before you put the eggs in the pot so you can control how soft the yolks will be. Pre-boiling your water also makes the eggs easier to peel once they're done cooking, which is a total game changer.17 Jul 2019

    How long do eggs need to fully boil?
    How long to boil your eggs depends on what level of doneness you're going for. Set a 7-minute cook time for jammy eggs with set egg whites and firm but gooey yolks, or a 10-minute total time for eggs that are cooked through (but not chalky). You'll need a bit more time if you're using jumbo or extra-large eggs.8 Feb 2023
